Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.34,0:00:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We're producing this videotape informally out at the ranch.\NIt's not a studio production.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.57,0:00:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose is to merely illustrate the main points that we make in the book Power vs. Force.\NWe want to illustrate the technique of kinesiology, something about theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.45,0:00:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,something about its application in a great many different areas of life.\NSo this first videotape is a broad, general overview of the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.92,0:00:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And not in-depth on any one particular thing.\NThose will be separate videotapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the general overview, and as you'll see from the menu, which we'll follow shortly,\Nwe're going to touch briefly on a lot of subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.65,0:01:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The one we're going to explore most, of course, is consciousness itself,\Nbecause that's what the whole book is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.79,0:01:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I thought I'd just show you the basic technique of kinesiology.\NWe're going to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.65,0:01:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take theory to a different section.\NAnd the various subjects we're going to cover section by section.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.45,0:02:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But first is the basic technique itself.\NIt's very, very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.23,0:02:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask the person to hold out their arm.\NI usually use two fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.73,0:02:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I want to know their relative strength.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.16,0:02:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I always say resist.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.33,0:02:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now to make sure this is a suitable subject,\NI ask the person to picture someone they love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.36,0:02:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Close your eyes.\NPicture someone you love and resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.18,0:02:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNow picture some horrible event in your life or somebody you don't love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.53,0:02:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?\NPicture Adolf Hitler.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.69,0:02:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NAll right, a normal subject goes strong with love and goes weak with hate or fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.93,0:02:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a normal subject goes, hold, hold it here, I'm licking it in mine.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.43,0:02:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NHold Adolf Hitler in mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.53,0:03:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NAll right, a normal subject goes positive with positive stimuli.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And goes weak with negative stimuli.\NThis is very, very important to first test the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 2.4% of the population will give you the opposite effect.\NAnd this is a whole subject in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.61,0:03:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,These are people whose acupuncture system is totally blown out.\NTheir thymus gland is totally blown out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.30,0:03:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally, a normal person will give you a paradoxical response.\NThe way you cure that was figured out by Dr. John Diamond.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.87,0:03:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The negative, the paradoxical response, that is, something positive makes you go weak,\Nis due to an underactivity of the thymus gland, the immune suppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.90,0:03:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you get a normal person who's leading a normal life,\Nwho's not into criminality and negativity and heavy metal rock and drugs and stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.34,0:04:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they give you a paradoxical response,\Nyou can use what John Diamond, the Dr. Diamond, called the thymic thump.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.41,0:04:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You go, thymus gland is right.\Nhere it's the central organ of the immune system so if a person who's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.25,0:04:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,normal gives you a paradoxical response you smile think of someone you love and\Nyou thump over the thymus gland rhythmically three times you like this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.38,0:04:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha now when you retest the person they will go normal\Nexcept for 2.4 percent of population who won't go normal anyway all right so
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,first we make sure we have a normal test subject next we don't have any\Nextraneous extraneous stimuli in other words it's very important not to have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.89,0:04:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,music in the background it's best to be to get for accurate results you should\Nbe impersonal try not to radiate love and affection and laughter and that kind
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.62,0:05:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of thing because you don't want to get false positives you can have the subject\Nclose their eyes because what they're looking at might have an effect like
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.97,0:05:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,anything else\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.06,0:05:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,just takes a little experimentation when you're learning archery how to run a\Nvideo camera or what just takes a little experience it's a very very reliable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.06,0:05:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,technique as we've said elsewhere in these tapes it's been used by tens of\Nthousands of practitioners for over 20 years all around the globe all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,physicians and our neurologists and nutritionists physicians of all kinds\Nchiropractors it's extremely accurate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.94,0:05:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the only difference is the way it's been used up until the research I did was\Nmainly for material things and strictly physical phenomena and I'm really took
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.68,0:06:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it out to different dimensions so that's the technique and will demonstrate it in\Na variety of subjects okay well you're like a little radio and we're gonna get
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.77,0:06:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you to cut in and tell us what's playing in the field of consciousness so let's\Nsee you like these did you have some of those before no this switch is on now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.93,0:06:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see you like these did you have some of those before no this switch is on now\Nlet's see you like these did you have some of those before no this switch is on now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. First, we're going to just check this out.\NPut your arm out. Now resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.62,0:06:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now hold somebody you love in, hold your mom in mind.\NResist. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.51,0:06:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold somebody you don't like in mind.\NYou got somebody you don't like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.94,0:06:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody you're scared of?\NOkay. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.77,0:06:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes weak. She really goes weak.\NOkay. You like those, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.07,0:06:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you like them because you're eating them up.\NYou're eating them up for...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.06,0:06:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Look at the curtain.\NThe energy of these is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.67,0:06:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Resist.\NWell, all these will be sort of positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of what's in this is positive. Resist.\NYou're pretty strong when something goes positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.69,0:07:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she never does.\NYou can look at it if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at this guy and hold him in mind.\NNow resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold him. Resist.\NOkay. His energy is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.61,0:07:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Mr. Deutsch, who's head of the CIA.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.06,0:07:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very good news. Let's see.\NOkay. Here's a newspaper. It's got somebody's picture in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.54,0:07:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This man has positive energy. Resist.\NThis man has a negative energy. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the positive energy.\NThis man's energy calibrates over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.27,0:08:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 540.\N560.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.18,0:08:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,570.\NThis man's energy calibrates over 560.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.22,0:08:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you study about him in school?\NYou know what that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.62,0:08:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Abraham Lincoln.\NAbraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.95,0:08:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Abraham Lincoln.\NWhere's those nasty things?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.63,0:08:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here they are.\NHold those over your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.83,0:08:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of this product is positive. Resist.\NYou think you're going to smoke them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.13,0:08:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThey make you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.96,0:08:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They make you go weak.\NWho wants to smoke something that's going to make you go weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here's something interesting.\NDid you ever see these before?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.47,0:08:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NAll right. Let's just say
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.05,0:08:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of what you...\NYou can look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.17,0:08:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of what you're looking at is positive. Resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:08:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She went weak but manufactured tobacco.\NLook at the kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.79,0:09:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this was grown organically.\NWhat I'm trying to demonstrate here with this tobacco
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.25,0:09:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the response is not only the opposite\Nof what the individual believes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.82,0:09:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The response is the opposite of what everybody believes.\NEverybody thinks that this causes cancer and yet you went positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.59,0:09:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we are merely demonstrating is\Nthat the answer will be the same no matter what a person's belief system is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.72,0:09:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tested this a lot of times\Nand a group of 20 people all convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.87,0:09:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that tobacco causes cancer\Nand yet when I hold this organic,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.27,0:09:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,hold that over your tummy,\Nthe energy of this is positive. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.20,0:10:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of this is negative. Resist.\NSo, despite the fact that everybody has a very strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.79,0:10:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,reinforced belief system,\Nthe answer we got was exactly the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we're demonstrating then is\Nthe impersonality of this response.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.48,0:10:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a letter I wrote about some guy.\NI don't even know his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.78,0:10:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We came to a meeting.\NThis man's energy is positive. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.84,0:10:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This man's energy is negative. Resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we get the same answer.\NShe doesn't know anything about any of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know any of the people.\NIt's just as valid in kids as it is in adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.20,0:10:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And, again, what we're testing\Nis the capacity of this field
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.51,0:10:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to detect the differences between truth and falsehood.\NWe'll add something that I wrote about in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:11:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To become acquainted with the contents of this book here,\Nto become familiar with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.88,0:11:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to become familiar with it,\Nto read that book and sort of get it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.10,0:11:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,raises a person's level of consciousness. Resist.\NIt raises it over 20 points. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.58,0:11:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,30 points. Resist.\N35 points. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.67,0:11:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,37 points. Resist.\NNow, the interesting thing is,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.22,0:11:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who's ever heard the lectures or read the book,\Ntheir own level of consciousness jumps 35 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.22,0:11:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the average lifetime,\Nthe average person on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.99,0:11:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,during their lifetime,\Ntheir level of consciousness advances over 5 points. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.27,0:11:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Does not.\NIt advances over 4 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.44,0:11:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,5 points.\N6 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.75,0:11:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person's level of consciousness\Nadvances exactly 5 points in one lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.46,0:12:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And, therefore,\Nmerely to become familiar with the truth about consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.96,0:12:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,seems to jump a person's own level of consciousness 35 points.\NSo, to read the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.22,0:12:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time you finish the book,\Nyou won't be the same person who started the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.08,0:12:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second time you read the book,\Nyou will be a person of more advanced consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.08,0:12:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the book will make a lot more sense the second time through.\NI thought I'd just take something out of the current news.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.08,0:12:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to start with archaeology.\NStart with archaeology,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.24,0:12:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because it just so happened that\Non TV the other night, I think it was Channel 8,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,was a whole program on Atlantis.\NArchaeologic research.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.84,0:12:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Plato, 2300 years ago,\Nwrote about the lost continent of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.84,0:13:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he said that Atlantis existed 9,000 years before.\NHowever, we feel,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.58,0:13:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or the program brought up,\Nthat he's probably off one decimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.58,0:13:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was probably 900 years before, not 9,000.\NDifferences of one decimal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,occur like in Britain and the United States.\NThere's a difference of one decimal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.87,0:13:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as to what constitutes a billion.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The program brought this up.\NDid Atlantis exist 9,000 or 900 years before Plato?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.19,0:13:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's just ask that question.\NOn the program it asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.57,0:13:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll ask now,\NPlato was correct in stating that Atlantis existed 9,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to his existence.\NMore accurately,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.70,0:13:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a difference of a decimal there.\NWhat he meant in our use of numerology
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.17,0:13:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,was 900 years before this.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.69,0:14:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the program brought up various places Atlantis could be.\NLet's ask these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.91,0:14:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Atlantis is located under Antarctica, resist.\NAtlantis is located near Bimini, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did they say it was?\NThey said it was more likely located in the Aegean Sea, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.\NThat's what they said probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Near the island of Thera, resist.\NWas it the same as the old city of Akroteria?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.80,0:14:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Akroteria, resist.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.37,0:14:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo this suggests that archaeologically Atlantis existed in the Aegean Sea
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.08,0:14:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was outside the streets of Gibraltar.\NBut it doesn't say from what direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.14,0:15:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's another interesting thing here.\NThis week's newspaper says,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha's birthplace found in Nepal, archaeologists say.\NThis is a correct location, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually the Buddha's birthplace, resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.54,0:15:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that I don't ask questions.\NI make a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So in using the technique,\Nwe always make a statement, a positive statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.96,0:15:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the inaccuracies that people write me\Nthat they're not getting accurate results
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,are due to the fact that they ask questions.\NIt's very easy to lapse into asking a question,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,like, is this the correct place for the Buddha's birthplace,\Ninstead of just making a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.74,0:16:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the archaeologic applications, of course, are endless.\NAnd this film has to be of a certain limited length,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,so we could spend one entire videotape\Njust checking out archaeology
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.83,0:16:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and primitive drawings and caves\Nand the ancient caves
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.69,0:16:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in France.\NAnd we can go back into paleontology
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.36,0:16:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and track down, you know, the various artifacts\Nand date them as their exact age
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.46,0:16:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the various skulls\Nand things that have been found in Africa and elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.12,0:16:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the archaeologic applications are pretty endless.\NLet's go on to art.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.61,0:16:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have some interesting current things\Nhaving to do with art.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance,\Nin a recent Time magazine here,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.38,0:17:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a new Cupid.\NAnd is it really a Michelangelo?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.79,0:17:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NSo here is a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.86,0:17:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That Cupid is actually a Michelangelo.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.59,0:17:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not a Michelangelo.\NHere is a piece of original art.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to hold that over here so it reflects this?\NThis is a genuine piece of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a genuine Salvador Dali resist.\NLook at the signature here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.01,0:17:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That is actually Dali's signature resist.\NThat's good to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:18:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because when you invest in art,\Nyou're often talking about very large amounts of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.01,0:18:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a genuine piece of art resist.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.40,0:18:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is authentic resist.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.92,0:18:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the name here?\NPicasso.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.92,0:18:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NLook at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.55,0:18:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a genuine autograph resist.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.61,0:18:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We can ask the question now in reverse.\NThis is actually a very clever fake resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.61,0:18:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWhen you're investing several million dollars,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.93,0:18:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really good to know.\NThere are three paintings at the National Museum of Washington right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.07,0:18:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the authenticity of which is being disputed.\NSo using this technique here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.98,0:18:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can see,\Nyou could arrive at an answer rather quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.65,0:18:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought some applications in business might be useful.\NIt might be very interesting to just briefly run through.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.22,0:18:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see,\Neach one of these could take us all afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.92,0:19:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's an interesting business application\Nthat is very practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.11,0:19:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a few checks I got in the mail.\NHold that over your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.35,0:19:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a good check, resist.\NAs you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.58,0:19:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it was rejected,\Nlack of sufficient funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.80,0:19:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NHere's a proposition asking me
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.27,0:19:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept a transfer of $320,000 from Nigeria.\NThis is a legitimate business proposition, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.68,0:19:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a criminal enterprise, resist.\NThis is a criminal enterprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.40,0:19:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It just so happened that there was a TV program about this.\NIn Nigeria,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:20:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there's some peculiarity of the corporate\Nand business laws
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that allows them to do this kind of thing,\Nand they apparently have made a lot of money
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.39,0:20:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,on a lot of people.\NI thought we would ask something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.01,0:20:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just ask,\Nwhat is the integrity of this publisher, resist?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.04,0:20:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's good to know.\NVeritas Publishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.61,0:20:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So before you invest in something,\Na stock, a bond,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.75,0:20:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,before you use a certain investment counselor,\Nyou can check out the integrity of that particular enterprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.79,0:20:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that broker,\Nor that stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.79,0:20:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought for the first time\Nsome mutual fund,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.36,0:20:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,some mutual funds.\NLet's see, what was the name of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.42,0:21:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NThis is an integrates fund, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.29,0:21:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good to know.\NAll right, so what I just,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.51,0:21:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what I want to demonstrate is that the response\Ndoesn't have anything to do with my verbalizing the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.51,0:21:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with my holding it within consciousness.\NI don't have to tell you the name out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.22,0:21:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can keep it in my mind,\Nand we'll get to the reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.64,0:21:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings us to the subject of consciousness itself.\NSome explanation is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that consciousness,\Nwe calibrated here the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We could zoom in on that.\NAnd on page 52 of the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.83,0:21:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this map appears.\NI just wanted to show you that we can recapitulate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.16,0:22:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,These are actually,\Nyou see, consciousness is like a potential energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.16,0:22:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and within it are so-called levels,\Nwhich we call attractor,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.41,0:22:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,attractor fields.\NThat comes out of nonlinear dynamics and chaos theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.35,0:22:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get more into that in the section where we talk about theory,\Nbut what chaos theory discovered was
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.20,0:22:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that behind what appears like random data,\Nthat there is actually an organizing pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.70,0:22:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The most random data I can think of\Nis the entire field of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.10,0:22:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the human dialogue throughout history,\Nor through the current newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.10,0:22:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or the news broadcast,\Nit looks totally chaotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.55,0:22:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of bizarre things happen.\NThere seems to be no rhyme or reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.55,0:23:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Human behavior doesn't really make sense.\NSomebody says they're going to be here at 1230.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.31,0:23:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's now quarter one, and they aren't here yet.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.31,0:23:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears chaotic.\NBut behind it, there are organizing patterns.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.50,0:23:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the main things we did in the book was\Nprovide some kind of a map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.50,0:23:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and we used kinesiology to do it.\NThe reason we used kinesiology to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.92,0:23:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is because consciousness itself\Nhas no dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.31,0:23:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself...\NYou see, in quantum theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.57,0:23:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,when you go beyond the smallest particle\Nand the smallest energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.57,0:23:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you go beyond locality,\Nand therefore you're beyond space
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.67,0:23:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're beyond time.\NSo anything that happens within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.67,0:24:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is, you might say, recorded there forever.\NSo that means that we could recapitulate these levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.03,0:24:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just do that.\NIt's on page 52 of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.58,0:24:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just stand back and let him zoom in a little bit on that.\NThe critical level is courage at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.80,0:24:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?\NSo let's say...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.80,0:24:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say pride is over 200. Resist.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.76,0:24:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride is over 170. Resist.\NPride is about 175. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.83,0:24:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride is over 176. Resist.\NAlright. Pride is about 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.08,0:24:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger is over 125.\N140.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.48,0:24:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,145.\N150.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.48,0:24:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do it again.\NAnger is over 149.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.30,0:24:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,150.\NAnger is about 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.97,0:24:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say fear.\NFear is over 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.06,0:24:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,98.\N99.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.25,0:25:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,100.\NFear is about 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.45,0:25:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can recapitulate all these levels.\NEverything below 200 makes you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.34,0:25:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride, anger, desire, fear,\Ngrief,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.34,0:25:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy,\Nguilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.34,0:25:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,shame.\NAnd all the variations of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.75,0:25:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything from 200 up makes you go strong.\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.43,0:25:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So...\N250 is neutral. Let's ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.07,0:25:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At neutral...\NNeutral is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.47,0:25:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if it's this way and it's okay if it's that way. Resist.\NSee, that's a positive feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.88,0:25:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutral.\NIf I get the job, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.88,0:25:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I don't, I'll get another job. See?\NIf you're at anger, you're angry because you didn't get the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.10,0:25:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in pride, you're arrogant about it.\NIf you're in fear, you're too fearful to pass the interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.17,0:25:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in grief, you didn't get the job, so you're going to kill yourself.\NApathy is...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.17,0:26:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's hopeless. There's no jobs around.\NShame is, well, I don't have a job, so I'm ashamed to be seen in public, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.96,0:26:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, neutral is okay.\NWilling is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.96,0:26:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Willing is around 310. Resist.\NReason is around 400. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.50,0:26:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Science is about 400. Resist.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.89,0:26:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we don't have Reason on?\NOh, yeah, we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.98,0:26:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Love starts at 500 and goes on up to 1,000. Resist.\NUnconditional love is about 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.29,0:26:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy is about 580.\NPeace of God is about...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.61,0:26:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is what? 600.\NEnlightenment is 600 to 1,000. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.35,0:26:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's check on kinesiology itself.\NThe energy level of kinesiology itself as a technique is approximately 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.57,0:26:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,500. Resist.\NYes, it's 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.02,0:26:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of truth...\NI've never asked this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.02,0:27:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of truth of this map of consciousness here calibrates over 500. Resist.\NOver 600. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.16,0:27:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 700. Resist.\NOver 800. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.16,0:27:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 900. Resist.\NThe arm okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.69,0:27:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates about 840. Resist.\NHuh, that's interesting. That's the level of...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.28,0:27:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of the book, I think.\NThat's the level of the consciousness of this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.32,0:27:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 700, 800, 840, 850.\NThat's the level of consciousness of the book itself, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.88,0:27:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, now, the consciousness has no dimension.\NIt's beyond space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.31,0:27:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason it works, kinesiology works, is it has to do with causality.\NWe're going to have to get into causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.30,0:28:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to get into that more later.\NWhat the world thinks is that causality moves from A to B to C.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.71,0:28:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In this direction, see?\NActually, causality does not move that way at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.96,0:28:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It moves from consciousness into the world as ABC.\NSo causality does not work horizontally in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.01,0:28:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It works in this direction.\NSomething that's held in consciousness, then it manifests in the visible world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.24,0:28:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me show you that.\NI'm a flower unfolding like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.65,0:28:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThis precedes this and is a necessary condition to reach this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.03,0:28:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But this does not cause that.\NSo what the world thinks when it sees ABC sequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.38,0:29:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,what it thinks is causality is not causality, it's a condition.\NThe condition for B to appear is preceded by A, but it is not caused by A.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.85,0:29:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we have a flower growing, then a bigger flower growing,\Nand then a bigger flower growing,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.21,0:29:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the smaller flower does not cause the bigger flower.\NAnd here's the full-grown flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.21,0:29:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These are stages, but it's not causality.\NTherefore, the whole theory of evolution is incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.33,0:29:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution has to do with A, B, and C.\NEvolution occurs in consciousness and then expresses itself downward.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.92,0:29:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get into causality later.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.51,0:29:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness is everywhere present.\NLet's say like a radio wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.03,0:29:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So anybody within that field would give us the same answer.\NThe question does not go in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.50,0:30:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We think the questions and answers go from person to person,\Nby their telephone, by their computer, or by asking them just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.33,0:30:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What actually happens is the statement or the image or whatever is held in mind,\Nand it goes to consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.50,0:30:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness then radiates it back to the other person.\NThere is no communication across this way at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.00,0:30:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than there is causality.\NIf I hold an image in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.00,0:30:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to even tell you what that image is.\NI can test you with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.31,0:30:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're connected to this consciousness,\Nyou will give me the response without even knowing what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.31,0:30:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NSo if I call somebody in a foreign land,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.66,0:30:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or the other side of the United States,\Nand I have two people there ready to test each other with kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.03,0:30:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say I'm holding something in mind,\Nwhat is the energy of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.29,0:31:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They will give me a response because of this,\Nnot because of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.45,0:31:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be because of this,\Nbecause they don't know what I'm holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.45,0:31:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's try it as an experiment.\NI want to just do that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.79,0:31:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, let's see.\NNumber six.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.58,0:31:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These new triangle things, I don't know.\NI'm going to hold something in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.40,0:31:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I want you to test...\NWhat's that guy that started the...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.94,0:31:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, Page. Okay.\NA fellow there by the name of Page,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.35,0:31:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm going to hold something in mind,\Nand I want you to test out the energy of the image I'm holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.22,0:32:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The image of what I'm holding in mind is positive.\NWhat do you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.79,0:32:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a true statement?\NIt's positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.67,0:32:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hold another image in mind.\NI want you to test that image.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.49,0:32:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you get?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.34,0:32:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NMake a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.61,0:32:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a statement.\NThe image that Doc is holding in mind is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.51,0:32:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd then just tell him to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.98,0:33:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you get?\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.07,0:33:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm holding an image in mind.\NThe image that I'm holding in mind is...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.83,0:33:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to say it's positive.\NCheck out the truth of the statement I just made.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.09,0:33:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not positive.\NIt's Adolf Hitler, so I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.63,0:33:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The first image I gave you was Lincoln, positive.\NHitler, negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.88,0:34:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Any questions you want to ask as long as we're on the phone?\NI'm holding a substance in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.03,0:34:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThe energy of what I'm holding is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.63,0:34:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Just make that statement to him,\Nand then test him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.07,0:34:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just tell him to resist.\NYes, it's positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.00,0:34:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe image of what I'm holding in my hand now is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.11,0:34:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Check that statement.\NSee if that's a true or false statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.90,0:35:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a true statement.\NNo, not a true statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.00,0:35:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's interesting.\NI'm just explaining on the blackboard here
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.28,0:35:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness, you know, has no dimension.\NAnd you see, the way it works,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.30,0:35:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I've ever explained it to you,\Nis when I hold an image,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.30,0:35:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it goes into the field of consciousness.\NThen when you test him,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.84,0:35:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he's connected to the same field of consciousness,\Nso he tests out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in other words,\Nit's like my thought goes into the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.80,0:35:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he gets the thought out of the water.\NBut the thought doesn't go between me and him,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.80,0:35:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?\NAnyway, I'll get to explain that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.15,0:35:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thanks a lot for cooperating with this little experiment.\NBye.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.15,0:35:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that was just a fun thing,\Nreally just to demonstrate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.51,0:35:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic theory, see?\NIt has to do with causality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.71,0:36:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and various interesting things.\NSo, that's a general theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.61,0:36:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a general theory.\NI wanted to demonstrate a few of the things that happen
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.86,0:36:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence.\NIn the book, I talk about critical factor analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.86,0:36:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if we focus in\Non a specific project,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.28,0:36:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't necessarily have to do anything in the world\Nto make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.78,0:36:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a basic principle, isn't it,\Nin spiritual teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.78,0:36:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What you hold in mind tends to materialize,\Ntends to actualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.78,0:36:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask that question.\NWhat you hold in mind tends to actualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.94,0:36:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NSo, the people who hold negativity in their minds
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.94,0:36:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to experience a life of negativity.\NThere's a section of a small town
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.32,0:36:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,not far from here.\NEverybody who lives there
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.80,0:37:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,has the same kind of a life story.\NEverything goes wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.80,0:37:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything goes wrong.\NEverything is always breaking down.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.80,0:37:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They have all kinds of warrants.\NThey're always in trouble with the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.59,0:37:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Their fences don't hold up.\NTheir dogs wander off and bite people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.59,0:37:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's just one endless negativity after another\Nbecause in this world, that's what happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.59,0:37:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is negativity.\NOther people will tell you that everything happens
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.63,0:37:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by synchronicity.\NJust as they think bobby pin, they open the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.92,0:37:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, they're not even thinking it.\NThe thought comes up, somebody says,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.92,0:37:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what about a bobby pin?\NYou open the door and your hand is on a bobby pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.92,0:37:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's synchronicity.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.32,0:37:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to save time,\Nto save time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.84,0:37:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, all you have to do is hold the thing up here\Nbecause to actualize it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.84,0:37:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can be quite a formidable undertaking.\NWhen we talked about causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.86,0:38:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we said things do not operate ABC.\NThe Empire State Building was held
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.88,0:38:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind by the consciousness of its creator.\NThat then manifested in this direction
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.76,0:38:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and manifested out in the world.\NSo, let's take a few pet projects I've had over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.42,0:38:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and didn't have time to actually do anything about it.\NIt always annoyed me when I was setting the VCR
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.86,0:38:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that when you run a TV station,\Nwhen you run through the stations,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.86,0:38:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing that identifies the station.\NSo, the only way you could tell what number you're setting it on
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.44,0:38:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,would be to look at the TV guide, see?\NSo, I always thought, wouldn't it be neat
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.21,0:38:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if these stations would put a little logo\Nin the lower right-hand corner
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.21,0:38:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or the lower left-hand corner?\NWhy don't they have a little logo going there
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.36,0:38:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what the program is?\N24 hours a day, they should have their logo there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.36,0:38:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And to make it even better,\Nthey could have the time and the temperature,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.36,0:38:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, little figures under there or something.\NSo, when I'm going to set my VCR
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.69,0:39:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm looking for Channel 5,\Nwhy do I have to look up that there's a cowboy program
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.69,0:39:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and run through all the programs\Nto find a cowboy program
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.69,0:39:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and hope that's Channel 5?\NWhy don't they just have 5 in the lower hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.17,0:39:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I never had a chance to do anything about it,\Nbut I held it in mind rather strongly
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.17,0:39:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for a couple of years.\NNow, the logo suddenly appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.42,0:39:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They've never had a logo appear\Nin the lower corner of any TV station.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.42,0:39:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to wait till the station break,\Nusually on the hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.84,0:39:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a big 5 would appear, see?\NThey wouldn't even give you the station
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.92,0:39:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on the half hour most of the time.\NA very big annoyance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.92,0:39:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I just held that in mind,\Nhow nice that would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.05,0:39:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, in fact,\Nall the channels have their little logo there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.05,0:39:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working to perfect it\Nby holding the time and the temperature strongly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.05,0:39:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's just ask.\NThose logos appearing in the TV stations
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.44,0:40:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,would have appeared\Neven if I didn't hold that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.71,0:40:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it wouldn't.\NMy strongly holding it in mind is desirable
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.46,0:40:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of sending it out\Nis what was responsible for its appearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.46,0:40:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.51,0:40:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,People deny the strength of their own mind.\NWe all live in the world of our own creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.63,0:40:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of our own perception.\NNow, here is another pet project
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.63,0:40:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I had going on for quite a while.\NAnd again, I didn't have much time to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.59,0:40:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But the dominance of gangs of the inner city,\NI saw there was only one way,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.88,0:40:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,through critical factor analysis,\Nwhich I talk about in the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.88,0:40:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a very complex problem\Nhas within it exactly one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.07,0:40:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you put your finger on that one point,\Nso a giant clock works,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.07,0:40:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you can stop a giant clock works,\Nas complex as it looks,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.07,0:40:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if you know where to put your finger.\NSo let's take street crime and the gangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.96,0:41:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial of all the gangs\Nwas the Gangster Disciples of Chicago
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.96,0:41:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because they were politically organizing into PACs\Nand beginning to elect people to the city council.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.67,0:41:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Huge incomes of $100 million a day in drugs,\Ndominating.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.38,0:41:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I saw was that only by using RICO,\Nconspiracy law,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.51,0:41:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,could you stop the gangs.\NSo one member of a gang commits a crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.21,0:41:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you then arrest the whole gang for conspiracy\Nbecause I've treated a lot of gang members
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.23,0:41:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know that everything that that gang is planning\Nis known by everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.23,0:41:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really, they're all in consort.\NSo I sent out a letter
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.78,0:41:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to everybody from Janet Reno\Nto the federal judiciary,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.78,0:41:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the state judiciary,\Nthe governors of the states,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.03,0:41:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,prosecutors, district attorneys,\Nand it turned out to be quite a formidable task.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.21,0:42:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, well, I'll just concentrate on Cook County\Nbecause that's where the focus,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.21,0:42:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the fulcrum of all this is the United States\Nbecause the Gangster Disciples were spreading
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.21,0:42:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and becoming the largest gang in the United States\Nand coalescing with the gangs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.21,0:42:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in all the major cities in the United States.\NSo I began to image this as critical
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.40,0:42:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that RICO was the way to stop the gangs\Nand specifically the Chicago Gangster Disciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.67,0:42:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is run by a very politically brilliant murderer\Ncurrently in Joliet prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.55,0:42:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to now, nothing has effectively stopped the gangs.\NThey pretty much rule the big cities,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.55,0:42:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,have taken over the big cities,\Ndestroyed its economy, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.55,0:42:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So I began to image using RICO\Nall right, this last week,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.19,0:42:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it suddenly appears in the paper,\Ntwo weeks ago, January 29th, 1996,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.40,0:43:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Arizona Republic.\NTrial begins today for a gang
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.84,0:43:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that may be the largest in the U.S.\Nand what they're being caught on is conspiracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.84,0:43:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's ask.\NHolding in mind that RICO was the critical factor
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.26,0:43:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop the gangs\Nis what brought about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.65,0:43:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was manifested as that headline.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.11,0:43:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And yes, my holding in mind\Non the specific point
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.23,0:43:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and zeroing in and sending out letters\Nto critical people,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.50,0:43:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,almost everybody answered except Janet Reno.\NJanet Reno was glad to get my letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.19,0:43:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NNo, Janet Reno was not glad to ever get my letter
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.19,0:43:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because she never replied.\NI don't know if anybody else paid any attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.19,0:43:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's not even important.\NIt wasn't the sending out the letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.48,0:43:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask that.\NI never asked that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.71,0:44:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Was sending out the letters critical\Nto this resolution of an impossible problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.71,0:44:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.71,0:44:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasted my time sending out the letters.\NSo sometimes we can, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.03,0:44:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,put some effort into it in manifest world,\Nbut generally speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.07,0:44:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the holding in mind.\NThere was something else I did years and years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.07,0:44:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,when I first noticed this phenomenon.\NI was sort of into unicorn cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.21,0:44:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and I looked all over,\Nand you can hardly ever find a unicorn card anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.80,0:44:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I began to desire and image unicorn cards\Nand how great it would be if they were everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.23,0:44:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then unicorn cards appeared everywhere.\NDid holding that unicorn in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.40,0:44:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,make those cards manifest?\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.40,0:44:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure did.\NThe same with Expresso.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.40,0:44:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Expresso was very hard to find in the United States,\Nalmost anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.40,0:44:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I held in mind how great it would be\Nif Expresso was everywhere available.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.40,0:45:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can get it in the fast food stores.\NWith holding in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.40,0:45:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Expresso is partially responsible\Nfor its manifesting as widespread availability.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.88,0:45:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.88,0:45:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, what you hold in mind\Ntends to manifest if it's for the good of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.13,0:45:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just keep holding it in mind.\NEverybody knows this who's ever done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.13,0:45:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Every place I've ever lived,\Nincluding this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.13,0:45:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,was imaged first.\NIt was a small little remote place
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.13,0:45:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,next to a creek,\Nin an arid place like Arizona,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.71,0:45:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the big place I had back east,\Nwas again imaged in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.71,0:45:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we hold in mind tends to manifest.\NThat's a very, very critical thing to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.63,0:45:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that 85% of the people on the planet\Ncalibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.73,0:46:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.\N85% of the people on the planet calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.13,0:46:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\N0.4% of the people calibrate 500 or over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.50,0:46:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NNow, that would sound quite alarming, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.71,0:46:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the people on the planet live here.\NAs far as 500 and up on additional love,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.92,0:46:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4% of the population.\NSo why doesn't the world destroy itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.44,0:46:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the power of the thought here\Nis so enormously powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.01,0:46:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that one person holding one loving thought at this level\Ntotally counterbalances maybe 50,000 people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.30,0:46:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,holding negative thoughts in mind.\NSo most of us think all kinds of negative thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.67,0:46:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the day.\NThis little fear, that little fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.67,0:46:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this little resentment or anger.\NAnd it doesn't destroy us
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.19,0:46:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because we also have a loving thought.\NWe also have a loving thought about our pets,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.53,0:47:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,about our friends or parents or whatever.\NSo one loving thought from this level up here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.05,0:47:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is so powerful that it prevents all these negative thoughts\Nthat we have throughout the day from actually destroying us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.05,0:47:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get what the consciousness level of mankind is right now.\NThe consciousness level, let's get it in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.69,0:47:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind in the year 1900\Nwas over 200, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.61,0:47:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year 1800, resist.\NThe consciousness level of mankind in the year 1700
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.19,0:47:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,was 190, resist.\NThe consciousness level of mankind in the year 1000
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.69,0:47:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was 190, resist.\NThe consciousness level of mankind stayed at 190
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.98,0:47:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for all the centuries until 1986, resist.\NAll right, in 1985, the consciousness level of mankind was over 200 resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.38,0:48:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1986, the consciousness level of mankind was 200, over 200 resist.\NBefore we leave this brief discussion of consciousness as a subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.55,0:48:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to say a little bit more about the map of consciousness and about causality\Nand relate a little bit more closely to the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.92,0:48:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book, it's quite obvious that positions from 200 and up are positions of power.\NPositions of 200 and down are positions of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.88,0:48:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes the difference is, for one thing, motive, intention.\NWhat is your primary goal? What are your highest values?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.63,0:48:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the basic law that you live by when the chips are down?\NAnd these are levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.03,0:48:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The lower levels are really levels of victimhood.\NThey all come about by virtue of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.84,0:49:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,As you take a position, you see, you limit your perception.\NSo these are all levels of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.09,0:49:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,These are very limited levels of perception in which you scope in on a very, very small piece of reality.\NAnd as you live from a higher view of, let's say, identifying with the good of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.88,0:49:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up towards the top of the calibrated scale.\NSo let's see what we mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.09,0:49:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say an unfortunate incident happens to you.\NLet's say you lose some money or you make a deal and somebody doesn't pay you the money back, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.07,0:49:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you could adopt any one of these positions, you see, depending on what your priority in life would be.\NYou can be ashamed of the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.76,0:49:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can not bring it up.\NYou can feel hopeless about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.38,0:50:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can feel guilty and berate yourself.\NYou can feel apathetic that it's hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.84,0:50:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to be done about it.\NYou can go into grief and wail about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.86,0:50:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ours is a crybaby society.\NEverybody likes to go into these victim roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.76,0:50:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get angry about it.\NYou can get indignant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.96,0:50:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody talks about rights.\NSo rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.57,0:50:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls in here somewhere, you know, having to do with anger and pride.\NThis is my right to do something or other.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.46,0:50:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See, right has is a rather limited perception because you can look at the same event from the position of responsibility.\NResponsibility is way up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.26,0:50:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,To a person who's responsible, right is just part of the picture and usually sort of an irrelevant part of the picture.\NThey're not concerned with rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.01,0:51:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Down below, people are preoccupied with right and wrong, with morality, with good and bad, and classifying things in those categories.\NCourage, for the first time, is the capacity to look at both sides of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.13,0:51:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person might be, down here, might be indignant.\NA person might be into rage, say, let's sue them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.09,0:51:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A person might be arrogant about the whole thing or fall into denial.\NThat courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.44,0:51:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to look at both the upside and the downside.\NEverything has a consequence and you may decide either to act or not act.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.13,0:51:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutral is a position of, sort of, it's okay if you take action.\NIt's okay if you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.59,0:51:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really not all that important.\NWillingness is willingness to look at it from a higher and a broader viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.80,0:51:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance might be that that's the nature of life.\NReason might be taking the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.30,0:52:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The intelligent view of it.\NOne's love for one's fellow human being may preclude taking any action.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.40,0:52:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say somebody takes a piece of your property and wrecks it.\NThis has happened to me in the not-too-distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.46,0:52:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A past, rather.\NAnd it was quite a sizable loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.01,0:52:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have gone into any one of these positions here, you see.\NHowever, I happen to know that the person has no money whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.57,0:52:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, frankly, I didn't even see...\NI didn't see the point of bringing it up with the person, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.21,0:52:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you could say it's my right.\NI could have taken a position that is hopeless to bring it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.21,0:52:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have gotten arrogant about it.\NI could have gotten angry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.28,0:52:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But the real thing is I love that person and I knew that if I brought this up to that person's awareness,\Nthey would have gone into guilt and shame about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.34,0:53:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you really love somebody, if they can't do anything about a situation,\Nthere's really no point to bringing it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.92,0:53:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you would be throwing them into the bottom of the box here,\Nwhere they're going to feel guilt and shame about something which is already past.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.92,0:53:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't do anything about it.\NAnd they don't have the assets to correct it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.92,0:53:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, the loving thing to do would be, in this particular instance, just overlook it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.28,0:53:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And accepting that that's the way life goes.\NYou can't drive your car, you know, 10,000, 20,000 miles a year without sooner or later getting a dent in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.28,0:53:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, those are the things, the wear and tear of life.\NTaking that position keeps a person sort of in a state of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.55,0:53:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the joy there?\NThe joy is that one is no longer at the effect of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.55,0:53:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,From 200 down, one is the victim of the world.\NBecause happiness is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.01,0:54:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is out there.\NThese are levels, let's say, of revenge and getting even, of jealousy, possessiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.19,0:54:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get the job, so and so.\NIf you get the job, so one's self-esteem, one's level of being is dependent on consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.48,0:54:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on how a thing turns out.\NIf you get the job, don't get the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.48,0:54:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the money, you don't get the money.\NYou get the girl, you don't get the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.63,0:54:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, one is the victim of consequences in the world.\NAs we see from causality, as we get, we'll talk a little bit more about that before we leave this subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.94,0:54:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What determines an external event is millions and millions of things.\NIn fact, it takes the entire universe to bring about a certain consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.51,0:54:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To be at the effect of that, to be the victim of that, then, is to be like a leaf thrown about in the wind.\NAnd we know lots of people whose emotions, from hour to hour, day to day, week to week, month to month,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.51,0:55:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are buffeted about by the arrows of fortune and fate.\NIf things go well, they're up. If things are down, they're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.65,0:55:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, from 200 and up, you begin to transcend the world.\NAnd from about 350 on up, you begin to re-own your power.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.13,0:55:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,These positions down here are those of powerlessness.\NBecause what happens to you is what goes on out in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.13,0:55:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You've projected your own power into the world.\NOnce you get to about 350, which is acceptance, you begin to own that you yourself are the source of your own happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.19,0:55:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave an example in the book of all these different ways of responding to finding yourself in jail, let's say.\NYou can hang yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.36,0:55:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become very spiritual.\NYou can join a 12-step group and become quite enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.65,0:56:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become very intelligent.\NYou can go to the law library and earn a degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.61,0:56:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There are all kinds of different ways we can handle the same circumstance,\Ndepending on what your overall motivation towards life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.61,0:56:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, these are levels.\NThese are levels of very limited perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.88,0:56:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,These are also levels of selfishness and egocentricity.\NThese are all levels of me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.88,0:56:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the beginning of the levels of us.\NAnd these are the levels up here of really the good of all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.38,0:56:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What will the impact of my actions be on humanity as a whole?\NSome people who have had a hard time in our society,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.09,0:56:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,have had it because they were acting, let's say, from the good of all mankind.\NLinus Pauling, who I knew, he and I had done a book together back in the 70s.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.21,0:56:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He won the Nobel Prize twice.\NOnce for chemistry and once for peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.46,0:57:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When he stood alone in front of the White House,\Nit was in the middle of the McCarthy era,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.92,0:57:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and he stood against nuclear testing\Nbecause the nuclear fallout, the radioactive fallout,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.13,0:57:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,had a deleterious effect.\NNot all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.13,0:57:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't interested in any of these lower levels.\NI want to go back to consciousness itself a little bit again.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.03,0:57:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure we understand it.\NI want to go back to causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.36,0:57:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We said within the world,\Nthis is the Newtonian paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.63,0:57:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Newton defined for us a four-dimensional world,\Nthe world of the computer, of mathematics and science.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.40,0:57:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates in the 400s.\NNewton himself calibrates at 499, as does Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.69,0:57:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of reason.\NIt takes you up to this level here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.98,0:58:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason, all the greatest scientists who have ever lived calibrate around 499.\NAnd that's the world of science in which A causes B causes C.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.88,0:58:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we go beyond that level of awareness,\Nyou see, that's a limited perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.86,0:58:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A limited perception of awareness.\NAs we get into the higher 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.86,0:58:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we start becoming aware of chaos theory,\Nnon-linear dynamics, fuzzy logic, set theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.86,0:58:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As we get to the high 400s,\Nwe get to a level such as the advanced theoretical physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.86,0:58:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics as described, let's say, by David Bohm.\NSo, Bohm, his thinking, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.19,0:58:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is right on the level of,\Nlet's say, beyond 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.19,0:58:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already into the 500s.\NHe has become aware of the difference in causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.15,0:58:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How does cause work?\NWell, within the visible world,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.15,0:59:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the manifest material world as we see it,\Nthere is no cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.34,0:59:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a shocking shift of paradigm\Nwhen you hear it for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.36,0:59:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're so used to thinking that A causes B causes C,\Nlike a set of billiard balls hitting each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.03,0:59:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes sort of a jump of paradigm\Nto realize that none of that is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.80,0:59:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As I showed you when I was going like this,\Nto show you an example of how a flower develops,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.88,0:59:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the cause is not within the manifest world.\NLet's say that cause originates in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.67,0:59:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that this sequence ABC\Nis held as a concept in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.50,0:59:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This ABC, now,\Nhas the power to manifest sequentially
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.53,1:00:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as this series ABC.\NCause proceeds from unlimited high power
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.01,1:00:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to lesser and lesser power into the material world,\Nlike a step-down transformer.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.80,1:00:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness and beyond consciousness,\Nthere is that which is called awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.96,1:00:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get back to this\Nwhen we get to the spiritual aspects later in the course.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.23,1:00:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness, then, is beyond consciousness even.\NConsciousness is potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.76,1:00:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with is and is not,\Nbeingness and non-beingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.76,1:00:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,existence and non-existence.\NAwareness is beyond all of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.09,1:00:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The highest power, then, is that of awareness,\Nwhich is infinite, always was, always will be,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.34,1:00:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to consciousness.\NWithin consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.59,1:00:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,arises the beginnings of form\Non the level of essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.80,1:01:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we might say this is more the level of essence.\NEssence, when run through the transformer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.46,1:01:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human consciousness,\Ncomes down through desire and tension
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.48,1:01:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and manifests within the visible world.\NWhen we see a sequence of billiard balls,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.03,1:01:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,such as ABC,\Nwhat we're seeing is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.03,1:01:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the causality manifesting\Nas this,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.32,1:01:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are preconditions.\NThese are conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.38,1:01:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The condition of B appearing in this series,\NA is a condition to it,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.19,1:01:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is not a cause of it.\NSo that when we talk about
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.63,1:01:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a flower, let's say,\Nthe flower here,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.69,1:01:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,he's this big a flower,\Nand now, a month later, he's this big a flower,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.69,1:01:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it's this big a flower,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.84,1:01:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Newtonian concept,\Nthis causes this,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.84,1:02:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and this causes this,\Nbut from a higher viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.92,1:02:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no cause involved.\NThese are both consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.90,1:02:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of this M field, you might call it,\Nmorphogenetic field.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.84,1:02:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution, if we check it out with kinesiology,\Nwe'll see this is so.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.61,1:02:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution takes place on the level of\Nmorphogenetic fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.57,1:02:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is like a pattern\Nheld within consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.57,1:02:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which then manifests out as its physical expression.\NEvolution does not take place
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.73,1:02:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,within the physical world.\NYou know, the tiger with the biggest jaws survives
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.80,1:02:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because he can eat more and kill more.\NThat's the theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.80,1:02:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, that's not how it happens at all.\NThis is necessary to understand
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.11,1:03:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if you realize that what we hold in consciousness\Ntends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.88,1:03:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're holding something up here,\Nit's going to tend to manifest,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.88,1:03:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,materialize,\Nand appear within the physical world.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.13,1:03:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can experiment with that\Nand prove that to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.13,1:03:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick something that you desire\Nthat would be good for life,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.13,1:03:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,good for mankind,\Nand just keep picturing it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.13,1:03:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,holding it in mind,\Ndesiring it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.13,1:03:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe draw it,\Nmaybe even write letters to people.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.13,1:03:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you mail them or don't mail them,\Napparently makes no difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.13,1:03:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the best thing to do is,\Nif you picture
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.13,1:03:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that the way to keep animals from getting lost\Nis by having some kind of a little radio transmitter,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.51,1:03:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody obviously held that in mind\Nbecause now you can buy them in the marketplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.51,1:03:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have a pet project\Nyou would like to work on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.51,1:03:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for your own sake\Nbecause the mind tends to be skeptical
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.51,1:04:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,about such things,\Nput it down in a notebook.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.57,1:04:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it down in a notebook\Nand then just wait for it to show up
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.57,1:04:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,within the visible world.\NI wanted to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.63,1:04:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,mention before we leave\Nthe subject of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.63,1:04:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that these numbers that are on here\Nare logarithms.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.63,1:04:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,These are logarithms\Nand the direction of the arrow indicates
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.63,1:04:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,whether this makes you weak\Nor it makes you strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.61,1:04:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes the difference\Nwith these levels
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.67,1:04:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you might call\Na person's level of vested interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.03,1:04:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,People say,\Nwell what sets my consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.07,1:04:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,or somebody else's consciousness\Nwhere it is?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.23,1:04:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you have a vested interest in.\NSo if people have a vested interest
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.57,1:04:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say at the level of pride\Nthey can blow up innocent women and children
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.71,1:04:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's a negative energy\Nin the name of the IRA, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.71,1:04:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They can wave the flag\Nand say it's patriotism
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.71,1:04:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually it's just arrogance\Nbecause they're placing
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.71,1:05:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,their own political viewpoint\Nabove the lives of innocent citizens.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.76,1:05:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So what it is you're willing to die for,\Nyour vested,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.76,1:05:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have a vested interest in.\NThese people here have a vested interest
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.76,1:05:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in being right at any cost,\Nbeing right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.76,1:05:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's their vested interest.\NSo they're willing to sacrifice love,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.69,1:05:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,marriages, joy, positions, jobs\Nfor being right, being right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.84,1:05:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's where you set your power\Nis what you're willing to go for.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.09,1:05:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to recalibrate\Nthe power of an individual thought
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.09,1:05:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which has never been done\Nas far as I know ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.09,1:05:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just try it.\NAnd a thought at the energy level of 100,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.90,1:05:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,energy level 100,\Nbecause most people have lots and lots
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.15,1:06:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of fearful thoughts.\NThe power of that thought is between
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.28,1:06:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,10 to the minus 700\Nand 10 to the minus 800 million
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.30,1:06:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,microwatts resist.\NAt the level of 100
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.76,1:06:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a thought is more powerful\Nthan 1 to the minus the log
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.92,1:06:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,minus 10 to the minus 700 million resist.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.67,1:06:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a thought\Nat the level of love, 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.34,1:06:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A thought at the level of love\Nmeasures 10 to the minus approximately
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.78,1:06:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,35 million microwatts resist.\NSo the difference between
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.23,1:06:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,10 to the minus 35 million microwatts\Nand 10 to the minus
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.48,1:06:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,700 million microwatts,\Nthe difference in power is so enormous
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.48,1:06:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really beyond comprehension.\NBut the significance is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.76,1:07:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that a loving thought is so powerful\Nthat it contradicts thousands
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.76,1:07:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and thousands of negative thoughts.\NAnd if it weren't for that,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.76,1:07:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,then salvation would not be possible.\NWell, we've got Lydia here today,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.21,1:07:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,very fortunate.\NHi, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.21,1:07:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's been part of a research team\Nfor NBC
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.21,1:07:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that did a very famous documentary\Non PBS on the Sphinx
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.59,1:07:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and having to do with\Nthe age of the Sphinx
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.42,1:07:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and various other things.\NWhy don't you tell us
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.42,1:07:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what you've been up to?\NYeah, I'd be happy to.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.42,1:07:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you got that...\Nthe research you did won the Emmy Award,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.42,1:07:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand, for research.\NYes, we did.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.92,1:07:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, a colleague of ours,\NDr. John West,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.92,1:07:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,spent many, many years\Non the hypothesis
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.92,1:07:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Sphinx was older\Nthan anything else
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.92,1:07:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Giza Plateau.\NAnd he based his assumption
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.92,1:08:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on the fact that\Nit's weathered by water.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.92,1:08:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We finally have hard science\Navailable to us in this century
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.92,1:08:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to go and test his theory\Nand prove it out,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.92,1:08:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something we did in 1993.\NWhen we were at the Giza Plateau,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.92,1:08:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we happened to have\NDr. DeBecke
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.92,1:08:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Colorado School of Mines\Nuse his new infrared photography methods
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.93,1:08:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and his current\Nsonography methods
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.93,1:08:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to test what was under\Nthe Sphinx in the plateau.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.11,1:08:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And we found three man-made chambers\Nunder the Sphinx.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.11,1:08:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what this did for us\Nwas pose the question
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.11,1:08:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for the public at large,\Nhow did they get there?
