Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.93,1:20:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do that.\NThe gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.53,1:20:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.07,1:20:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you can locate any evidence anywhere.\NYou can ask if the gun's ever been fired, how many times it's been fired.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.48,1:21:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We can ask who owns the gun, if it's ever been used in a crime.\NIn other words, it's value.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.73,1:21:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And tracking a clueless crime is amazing, because a clueless crime, you haven't got any lead.\NSo here we can start with the lead.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.06,1:21:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do that on a different videotape sometime.\NWe'll really go into crime and evidence and forensics and verifying data and solve the crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.05,1:21:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We can tell who did it, whether they're black and white, whether they're male or female.\NWe can get the exact time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.02,1:21:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We get their intention, their motive.\NWe can ask where the booty is.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.14,1:21:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We can ask what weapons were used, whether the guns are loaded or not loaded.\NWell, of course, this is very useful to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.19,1:21:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if I'm a police officer and I have to go in on a suspected drug raid, I certainly want to know whether they've got guns.\NIf so, are they automatic rifles?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.42,1:22:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, are they, what kind of, I certainly, if I'm going to wear a bulletproof vest, I want to know, is it the kind of bullet that can go through a bulletproof vest?\NIn other words, I can, with kinesiology, research a whole crime area.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.57,1:22:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And go in at no risk to the life of anybody.\NYou can also figure out the best time to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.43,1:22:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they asleep now?\NDo they have guns there?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.27,1:22:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they have drugs on their premises right now?\NIn other words, it's used in criminal investigation and forensics and criminology and police work is rather, you know, unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.18,1:22:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we go into health, you know, current events is a place where kinesiology is really the most fun.\NYou can watch the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.60,1:22:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You can check out on the McNeil-Lehrer Hour whether somebody's telling the truth.\NAnd I just wanted to do the McNeil-Lehrer Hour because it's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.94,1:22:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I was once on that program.\NMcNeil-Lehrer Hour calibrates at 400 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.93,1:22:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over 450 resist.\NIt calibrates the low 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.81,1:23:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It drives me crazy with boredom because the thing about the low 400s is intellectualizing.\NPeople can yammer, yammer, yammer, intellectualize endlessly to the point of distraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.00,1:23:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter does it.\NShe can't stand listening to the McNeil-Lehrer Hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.11,1:23:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, Daddy, please.\NDon't play that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.31,1:23:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Current events is very interesting.\NSo we can watch the evening news.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.69,1:23:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night I think there was a program on pop bisexuality.\NLet's just check the energy of pop bisexuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.01,1:23:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NPop bisexuality is a positive thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.31,1:23:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Faddish bisexuality is constructive resistance.\NUgh.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.39,1:23:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Faddish bisexuality...\NBisexuality is detrimental to the health of society.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.43,1:24:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Pop bisexuality represents an advance in man's consciousness.\NPop bisexuality represents degeneracy in civilization.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.50,1:24:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a degenerate movement and it's phrased like it's very advanced,\Nlike we're becoming more sophisticated, more hip, more aware.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.15,1:24:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I mean, Rome did the same thing in many civilizations.\NIt got into degeneracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.23,1:24:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It got into health because almost everybody has an interest in health.\NAnd this is where kinesiology has been used the most.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.97,1:24:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Lily, come on over here.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.23,1:24:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The way kinesiology really started back in the 70s,\Nthe way it was used the most was for medications and health foods, things like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.15,1:25:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, we could take this apple, which is a commercial apple.\NThe energy of this apple is positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.21,1:25:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a commercial apple.\NIt's full of pesticides, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.81,1:25:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks pretty.\NLooks pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.30,1:25:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's spread that way.\NHere we have an organic apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.39,1:25:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no, I shouldn't have said that to you.\NI sort of blew it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.10,1:25:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have a different apple.\NThe energy of this apple is positive.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.88,1:25:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the relationship between organic and pesticides.\NThat's what we got here.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.97,1:25:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We can show it with one premise, you see.\NWhat people don't understand is that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.31,1:25:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when we...\NWhen we use this test subject for kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.19,1:25:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not testing the person.\NWe don't care what the person thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.15,1:25:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They're nothing but a conduit,\Nlike a wire,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.56,1:26:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,between consciousness in the invisible world\Nand the movement of the arm in the visible world.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.61,1:26:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It bypasses the person.\NSo what their opinion is, what their thoughts are...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.61,1:26:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take something and test it against a prevailing human belief system.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.09,1:26:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one that I think is very interesting\Nbecause it flies in the face of what people believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.01,1:26:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have a substance in this jar.\NPlease hold that against your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.42,1:26:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of this substance is positive for this.\NThis substance is injurious to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.78,1:26:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?\NThis is organic tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.78,1:26:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have commercial tobacco.\NThis commercial tobacco has a positive energy for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.84,1:27:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NHere we have a commercial tobacco,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.61,1:27:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's an organic tobacco.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.40,1:27:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of this product is positive for this.\NAmazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.18,1:27:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NLet's just take this and hold it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.92,1:27:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This product is injurious to your health.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.63,1:27:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do this again.\NThe energy of tobacco before 1957 was negative for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.02,1:27:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Before 1957, the energy of tobacco was positive for this.\NYes, the Indians have been smoking it for a long, long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.78,1:27:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandparents all smoked, and they lived in their late 90s.\NNobody ever heard of cancer of the lung or attributed it to tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.78,1:28:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe injuriousness of tobacco is due to a chemical placed on it,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.73,1:28:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's manufactured.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.72,1:28:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That chemical came into use in 1957.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.72,1:28:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That chemical is a fertilizer.\NThat chemical is a pesticide.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.89,1:28:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.97,1:28:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we get is what's injurious about smoking tobacco\Nis that a pesticide, which causes cancer, came into use in 1957.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.53,1:28:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And obviously, if you want to cure cancer of the lung,\Ninstead of trying to get people to stop smoking because they're not going to do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.40,1:28:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you remove the chemical that's injurious.\NAmazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.97,1:28:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, science has vested interests.\NWe talked about vested interests.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.97,1:28:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That limits truth.\NThe Center for Science in the Public Interest likes to propagate a lot of,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.26,1:29:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, it's propaganda about secondary smoke and all this kind of thing,\Nbecause they have an agenda.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.31,1:29:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So having to do with that,\Nthere was an article in Science magazine a month or two ago
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.81,1:29:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that one gram of vitamin C for the average adult\Nprotects the cells of the body from any injury from smoking.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.32,1:29:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Center for Science in the Public Interest didn't even publicize that.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.89,1:29:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's against their own political agenda.\NSo what people think is,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.89,1:29:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is a search for truth.\NScience, you know, is taking the place of religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.18,1:29:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And science, like anything else, is limited,\Nhas a political agenda,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.30,1:29:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,an ax to grind,\Nand they were really interested in the public health.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.10,1:30:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They should have widely advertised that all you smokers out there,\Nyou know, should smoke organic tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.18,1:30:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They should ask the manufacturing companies to find and remove that insecticide.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.85,1:30:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They should advise everybody to take a couple grams a day of vitamin C.\NIf you're going to smoke, take vitamin C.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.85,1:30:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NIf you're really interested in public health.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.75,1:30:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what's interesting is that you have a prevailing belief system\Nin society today that tobacco will give you cancer,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.32,1:30:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet when I hold this, I mean, you're a member of the prevailing society.\NOh, I definitely have prejudice against it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.32,1:30:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.\NSo, in other words, we've got an answer completely the opposite
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.32,1:30:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of what you believe and the rest of the world believes.\NIn fact, the only one who knows this, the facts about this, is me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.48,1:30:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The world doesn't know about it.\NI raised some organic tobacco myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.31,1:30:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and I tested, of course, the kinesiology,\Nand it's perfectly harmless.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.25,1:31:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind that's raised by the Indians is harmless.\NSo to further that research, it would be interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.38,1:31:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to check out the incidence of cancer in the long end societies,\Nprobably primitive societies that don't use chemicals.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.38,1:31:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is, if you don't use chemicals in raising the tobacco,\Nthe grasshoppers eat up about a quarter of your crop.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.78,1:31:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, there's a commercial reason for using insecticides.\NWell, maybe you can test and find a way to deter the grasshoppers.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.81,1:31:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think they should withdraw that chemical, you know,\Nand focus on truth instead of some political agenda.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.89,1:31:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Dr. Honkert, that's certainly an amazing thing to discover for us.\NWell, here's something that I particularly like.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.89,1:31:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!\NThe energy of these cookies is positive. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.46,1:31:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, my favorite cookies, and I've got eight boxes of them.\NThis one looks better.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.13,1:32:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a horrible little stale cookie from Christmas.\NHold this over your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.13,1:32:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of this cookie is positive. Resist.\NSee, so it doesn't have to do...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.06,1:32:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, this would be sort of a nasty old cookie to eat,\Nand this would be very, very delicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.60,1:32:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This obviously is made with, you know, chemicals and things like that.\NThis is obviously homemade with love.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.60,1:32:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was homemade. That's a homemade organic cookie.\NThe power of belief systems, you see, what causes many human diseases
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.15,1:32:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are common belief systems.\NI do a lot of examining lots of patients for Social Security disability
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.92,1:32:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and things like that.\NThere's a whole raft of diseases which are strictly iatrogenic,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.59,1:32:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, initiated by the medical profession,\Nand given power and strength and human consciousness by the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.59,1:33:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Half the diseases that afflict mankind today are caused by,\Ncreated by, the effect of the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.28,1:33:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just see if that's true or not.\NBreast cancer was relatively rare when I was an intern, resident.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.75,1:33:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The widespread publicity given to breast cancer\Nhas increased the incidence of breast cancer. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.03,1:33:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It has increased it absolutely.\NNot just because more cases are being discovered. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.02,1:33:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, a thought held in consciousness tends to manifest.\NNow, let's take some purely imaginary diseases.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.51,1:33:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Diseases that I've known forever are purely imaginary.\NAllergy is a physical disease. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.56,1:34:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All allergies are due to belief systems. Resist.\NYou know, you can give anybody an allergy by suggesting it to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.30,1:34:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Fill three of your towels around and here's Grandma saying,\Noh, everybody in our family is allergic.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.30,1:34:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These puffy eyes, I don't need to care.\NOh, me too. I had a fever. I was allergic to horses.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.30,1:34:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I got poison ivy.\NThose are all fake diseases.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.35,1:34:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not fake once you got them, but they're initiated by suggestion.\NAll right, so one thing we can say about human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.65,1:34:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is that consciousness itself, the consciousness itself has no form.\NIt hasn't been programmed yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.72,1:34:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the hardware in a computer.\NThen comes the programming in through the software,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.77,1:34:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the software being school, Mommy and Daddy,\Nyou know, what you overhear in the playground.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.56,1:34:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing about the hardware, the thing about consciousness itself\Nis that it's innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.97,1:35:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As you move up the scale of consciousness,\Nyou become aware that intrinsically everybody is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.06,1:35:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens then is on this innocent consciousness,\Nthese prevailing programs start to impale.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.31,1:35:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The little toddler, two years old, believes anything it hears.\NIt believes Mommy and Daddy. It believes Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.64,1:35:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It believes what it hears is a church.\NAnd perception becomes progressively limited
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.02,1:35:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as these belief systems begin to take hold.\NSo everybody is run by their software.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.85,1:35:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say that everybody is intrinsically innocent and naive.\NThey have no context of higher awareness in which to judge an incoming program.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.32,1:35:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the Center for Science in the Public Interest\Nprograms us with one disease after another,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.77,1:36:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,once held in consciousness, these now become very powerfully suggestive.\NHow can you prove this? It's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.01,1:36:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You put a patient under hypnosis, you can recreate any of these illnesses.\NAnd when you, in the non-hypnotic state, you can remove them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.57,1:36:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can say to a person that they have a very bad allergy to roses,\Nand they will forget about this when they wake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.35,1:36:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they wake up, I then walk in with roses,\Nand that person, their nasal passages will actually swell up.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.35,1:36:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The body will respond to the belief system.\NIn multiple personality disorder, we see a very interesting thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.89,1:36:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When one personality is there, the person has an ulcer.\NAnother personality may be an alcoholic, a drug addict, an infomaniac.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.89,1:36:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Another personality may be church-going and honest and have no allergies,\Ncan eat anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.27,1:36:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...\NThese are real things that really happen in the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.26,1:37:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So it finally has come to public awareness,\Nsomething I've known for a long time in examining a lot of these patients.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.68,1:37:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...\NSilicone breast, you know, silicone implant disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.68,1:37:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely fictitious. There is no such animal.\NUm...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.31,1:37:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Environmental disease, chemical disease.\NYou read...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.31,1:37:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, and these things typically show an epidemic pattern.\NUh...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.38,1:37:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One or two employees in a factory will complain that they can't breathe\Nwhen they got home that day or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.38,1:37:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon, six employees can't breathe.\NPretty soon, the company is removing all these things and putting special fillers.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.38,1:37:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more people come down with it.\NAnd what intensifies these things is compen...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.82,1:37:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if it's compensable, if you can collect from somebody.\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.82,1:37:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...\NThe propensity of the judiciary to place blame into the world
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.02,1:37:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and back up these kind of things.\NSo this is, you know, something I've been holding in awareness,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.06,1:37:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that these things are all fake.\NCome on over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.53,1:37:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NLast week, finally, my thought manifested.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.53,1:38:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that...\NYou know, in the previous section of this videotape,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.53,1:38:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,if you hold a thought in mind strongly enough,\Nand if that consciousness is high enough, it'll manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.53,1:38:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...\NIn the Arizona Republic, we have a whole article that says...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.21,1:38:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Beware the nocebo.\NThe nocebo acts like a placebo, only it's a negative thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.21,1:38:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And they use an example, another one called Gulf War Syndrome.\NOkay, let's ask about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.27,1:38:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NGulf War Syndrome is an actual physical disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.43,1:38:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NAh!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.43,1:38:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Orange is a...\NIs an actual physical disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.43,1:38:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NSilicone implant disease, which...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.69,1:38:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen patients with silicone implant disease,\Nand it's heartbreaking when you listen to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.96,1:38:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Their hair is falling out, they have buzzing in their ears,\Ntheir eyes gyrate, they can't swallow,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.96,1:38:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,everything makes them throw up, everything gives them constipation or diarrhea,\Nall their limbs are weak, all their muscles are shot,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.96,1:39:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all their joints are gone, their cartilages are dissolving.\NIt's one walking piece of pathology.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.07,1:39:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There is such a thing physically as silicone implant disease.\NThere is such a thing psychologically as silicone implant disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.06,1:39:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.57,1:39:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got people all over the place, you know, disintegrating,\Nand these people you see in the health food stores carrying oxygen on their back,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.82,1:39:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, because they're afraid to breathe the air.\NWhat's happened is they have programmed themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.38,1:39:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in with negative belief systems of such complexity that they can hardly move.\NThere's a community not far from here, the so-called bubble people,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.43,1:39:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, who board themselves up in their houses,\Nand they have belief systems that the rug will make, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.76,1:39:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the rug will kill you, the walls will kill you, the air will kill you.\NAnd, of course, we have the belief system that sunlight will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.76,1:39:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the sun will kill you.\NFresh air, sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.76,1:40:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Fresh air and sunshine, the woods come out over here.\NFresh air, fresh air, the sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.39,1:40:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,These people believe that sunshine is injurious.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.39,1:40:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Fresh air is injurious.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.39,1:40:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, how can you live in a world with a body?\NIn a bubble.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.71,1:40:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, everything you read in the health,\Nthe one thing I got away from health food and health food literature
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.71,1:40:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and a lot of holistic belief systems is because they tend to propagate a lot of this stuff,\Nthat insecticides and all this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.71,1:40:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.86,1:40:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.86,1:40:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.86,1:40:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.57,1:40:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.57,1:40:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.57,1:40:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.57,1:40:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.57,1:40:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.77,1:40:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.02,1:40:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.05,1:40:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.85,1:40:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You come out over here.\NNow, you test me.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.85,1:40:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's that thing with the pesticides?\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.85,1:40:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.71,1:40:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThis, you want me to ask if this is healthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.71,1:40:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, for me?\NThis, this apple is healthy for Dr. Hopkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.71,1:40:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes it is.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.71,1:40:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I canceled belief systems that pesticides have any power over me.\NNothing out there has any power over me.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.01,1:41:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm subject only to what I hold in mind.\NThere's nothing in the world that has any power over me.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.85,1:41:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not silicone.\NNot insecticides.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.01,1:41:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Not.\Nnot allergies, not danders, not pollens, like moles, all the things.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.96,1:41:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was once subject to all those things,\Npoison ivy, moles, danders, horse dander, dog dander, you know, all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.94,1:41:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you buy into a negative belief system,\Nthe only way you can get out of it is to constantly cancel it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.68,1:41:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So in looking at health, you know, let's talk, how does a disease happen?\NHmm, well, you have the prevailing level of consciousness of the person.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.90,1:41:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That level of consciousness means they're going to be firing off thoughts.\NThose thoughts, if they're negative thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.68,1:42:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,any time you hold a thought in mind that makes you go weak with kinesiology,\Nwhat happens is you're blowing the immune system.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.55,1:42:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're blowing a whole acupuncture meridian.\NYou are disturbing the energy of the organ energized by that acupuncture meridian.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.84,1:42:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So you hold a negative thought in mind.\NThat affects the emotional body.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.57,1:42:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotional body affects that energy around the physical body called the etheric body\Nthrough which the acupuncture system flows.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.10,1:42:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That subtly alters in a pathologic direction the physiology of the physical body organ.\NConsequently, the way people die and get themselves off the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.73,1:42:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is by holding negative belief systems and thoughts.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.14,1:42:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,People recover from every ailment known to mankind\Nby going back up the other way,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.46,1:42:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,by canceling negative thoughts,\Nby elevating their level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.71,1:43:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,by holding loving thoughts instead of negative thoughts.\NI myself did the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.30,1:43:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I got rid of everything.\NI used to think athlete's foot, you caught that in showers.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.85,1:43:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, then I did.\NAnd dandruff, you got it to barber.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.72,1:43:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had ulcers and diverticulitis and migraine.\NI had headaches.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.35,1:43:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I even had a pyelonylosis, which is something that's supposedly actually surgical.\NAll kinds of things wrong with the gastrointestinal.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.97,1:43:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so allergic when I was a kid to the belief, allergic to poison ivy,\Nthat I literally landed in the hospital for two weeks with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.77,1:43:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All those things have disappeared spontaneously and gone away.\NSo that one can cure oneself, I know people with advanced multiple sclerosis,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.31,1:44:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of different cancers,\Nall kinds of diseases that have refused the negative belief system.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.27,1:44:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to say it doesn't apply to me.\NI realize everybody out there believes that.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.18,1:44:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In doing that, for instance, I went out one time\Nand I dug up a whole plant of poison ivy
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.89,1:44:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and played with it on some TV program I was on.\NAt one time, that would have put me in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.64,1:44:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's probably the value of following some consciousness-raising program,\Nsuch as I use the Course in Miracles because it is such a common and easy one to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.31,1:44:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the workbook in the Course in Miracles.\NBecause when you get up to about Lesson 97,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.27,1:44:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find that people are no longer subject to going weak with supposedly negative stimuli.\NAlmost everybody will go weak with fluorescent lights, pesticides, all those kind of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.21,1:44:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But as your own consciousness reaches a certain level,\Nthe realization that you are the source of all these belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.43,1:44:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're what's empowering them,\Nyou then become immune to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.93,1:45:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we know from holistic health and alternative medicine,\Nit concerns itself not so much...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.72,1:45:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It concerns itself, of course, with the physical body,\Nbut it says that around the physical body there are energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.00,1:45:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Acupuncture, for one thing, is a method of influencing those fields.\NThat around the physical body there's an etheric body,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.51,1:45:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and around the etheric body there's an emotional body,\Nand around the emotional body there...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.72,1:45:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is a mental body.\NAnd beyond that there's something called the causal body.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.17,1:45:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so, consequently, when they're interested in doing healing,\Nif there's something wrong with the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.07,1:45:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there must, of necessity, be something wrong with the etheric body.\NSo they work with energies trying to correct the error on the level of the etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.39,1:45:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the physical body, the etheric body is like a blueprint\Nin absolute detail, right down to the molecular and submolecular of the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.52,1:46:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you can see...\NIf you can change the etheric body,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.93,1:46:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the physical body will conform with the etheric body.\NSo if I could move your ears up in the etheric realm,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.23,1:46:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as time goes on, your ears will slowly grow up\Nand you're going to say to occupy that space.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.47,1:46:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What's behind a good deal of holistic health practices\Nis influencing energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.06,1:46:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, each thing you see would be of a greater power.\NSo we would have...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.27,1:46:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We would say...\NRight beyond the physical body is the etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.73,1:46:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask, is that true?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.07,1:46:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never asked this before.\NIs beyond and through the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.96,1:46:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is there an energy field called the etheric body?\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.46,1:46:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it have more power than the physical body?\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.19,1:47:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It does.\NBeyond that is the emotional body.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.42,1:47:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?\NI mean, that is so.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.30,1:47:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond the etheric body is the emotional body.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.51,1:47:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrounding and going through it, there is also a body.\NThere is a body of energy called the emotional body.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.01,1:47:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NIs that where the supposed chakras reside in the emotional body?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.68,1:47:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NChakra system, is that within the etheric body?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.07,1:47:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's within the etheric body.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.31,1:47:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond the emotional body is that which is called the mental body.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.78,1:47:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that yet is the causal body.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.94,1:47:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that is the higher spiritual body.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.71,1:47:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.93,1:48:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that tells us how the disease process proceeds.\NIf I hold a negative thought in the mind, can that create a change in the emotional body?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.52,1:48:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NWhich, in turn, can cause a change in the etheric body?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.52,1:48:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NWhich, in turn, can cause a change in the physical body?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.31,1:48:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.44,1:48:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now you see the whole purpose of spiritual healing and psychotherapy to treat psychosomatic diseases and all.\NIf what I hold in mind in the mental body is more powerful than any of the bodies below it,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.93,1:48:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it will influence how I feel.\NYou know, how I feel is going to influence my etheric body,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.51,1:48:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and my etheric body is going to manifest as a disease of the physical body.\NAnd you can actually detect that because with kinesiology or with acupuncture,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.02,1:49:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you can directly measure the consequences of these negative thoughts on the acupuncture system.\NAnd each acupuncture meridian goes to a specific body organ system.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.01,1:49:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what I hold in mind in my...\NMy emotions about that then are obviously going to influence my physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.59,1:49:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That would also explain why one's spiritual position is more dominant than anything else.\NI remember when I was looking for some volunteers,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.82,1:49:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to give a lecture on a course in kinesiology.\NAnd this was at the clinic back east,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.38,1:49:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and there were some friends of mine hanging around, people I knew.\NAnd I said, I have to give this lecture tonight, and I knew they were going to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.76,1:49:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, can I...\NCan I use you as a subject?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.31,1:49:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, I usually demonstrate the effect of sweet and low and fluorescent lights and pesticides.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.38,1:49:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as I tried each of these things, none of them went weak.\NEverybody goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.46,1:50:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, I tested thousands of people in large audiences.\NEverybody went weak to sweet and low.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.88,1:50:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, whoa, what's going on here?\NWell, they were all studying the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.73,1:50:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Course in Miracles is a workbook.\NAnd it turned out that by the time they got to...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.89,1:50:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to Lesson 90, they were immune to most of the...\NThey wouldn't go weak with all the negative things
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.51,1:50:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that anybody in the world goes weak with.\NAnd so, I went back and sort of studied it specifically
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.42,1:50:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was sort of blown away by this.\NAnd it turns out around Lesson 76 in the Course in Miracles, in the workbook,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.85,1:50:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,once you pass Lesson 76 or so,\Nyou're no longer subject to anything except what you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.75,1:50:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, wow, that's curious.\NAnd I went back and looked at, I think it was 76, and it said,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.14,1:50:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only subject...\Nto what I hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.34,1:50:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All we're really talking about over and over again\Nis the use of kinesiology as a research tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.56,1:51:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say you want to go back in history\Nand check out the Amelia Earhart story,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.92,1:51:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or you want to check out the Lindbergh kidnapping,\Nor you want to check out how did Napoleon feel
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.19,1:51:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,before he went into the pyramid,\Nand how did he feel after he left the pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.76,1:51:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's said that in the pyramid,\Nhe had a vision of his ultimate...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.03,1:51:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,defeat at Waterloo.\NSome...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.02,1:51:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We could ask some questions about humanity in general.\NLet's ask a fun question.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.77,1:51:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Delmer, come on over here.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.55,1:51:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a fun question we want to ask,\Nand this is a fun one.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.00,1:51:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can trust the man in a suit and a white...\NYou can trust the man in a suit and a tie.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.80,1:51:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NI've gotten that over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.28,1:51:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a trustworthy man?\NIf the man puts on a suit and a tie,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.76,1:52:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he enters a domain of untrustworthiness.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.72,1:52:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHe becomes now the politician.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:09.84,1:52:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Nbusiness is ruled by what makes the bottom line,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.50,1:52:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nvending the truth for the benefit.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.55,1:52:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, expediency.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:21.47,1:52:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the suit and the tie is expediency.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.02,1:52:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the man who wears a suit\Nand a tie is expediency.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.50,1:52:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NThe law of the suit and the tie is truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.18,1:52:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NHe's not interested in truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.39,1:52:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The lawyer in court is not interested in truth.\NHe's interested in winning the case, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.02,1:52:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it has nothing to do with truth whatsoever.\NExposure to this videotape and reading the book
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.59,1:52:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Power vs. Force\Nraises one's level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.51,1:52:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,over 35 points.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:54.03,1:52:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,40 points.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.89,1:52:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Average of 36 points.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.50,1:53:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting,\Nbecause we talked the level of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.39,1:53:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,being at 190 over the centuries,\Nand it jumped in 1986 to 207.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.10,1:53:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And another interesting question we can ask is\Nconsciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.19,1:53:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a person is born with a level of consciousness.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.43,1:53:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll ask more about that later.\NBut there's actually a calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.55,1:53:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute you're born.\NIt's almost as though you enter the body
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.97,1:53:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or you activate the body\Nfrom a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.64,1:53:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,One obvious place that we can use this\Nis in intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:37.38,1:53:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,military,\Nespionage,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.61,1:53:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,various things like that.\NYou don't know who this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.32,1:53:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on over here a second.\NHold this against your sword, Plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.60,1:53:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This man is loyal to the United States of America.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.25,1:53:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This man can be trusted.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.38,1:54:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have a double agent,\Nthe inside story of the CIA's mole.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.13,1:54:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You have,\Nwe have another one,
